Stanbic IBTC Bank said that it would cap spending limit for offshore card transactions to $500 per month while cash withdrawals will be capped at $100. On the other hand, Zenith Bank announced the suspension of debit card use abroad for cash withdrawals albeit temporarily, while capping monthly spending limit abroad to $200. Other banks that have lowered the withdrawal limits for individual abroad include Ecobank and Fidelity Bank. A sharp drop in oil prices and exports, which accounts for 90 % of the countryâ€™s foreign exchange earnings, has left Nigeria with a dollar shortage. The Covid-19 pandemic has deteriorated the situation further due to restriction on international travel. Central Bank of Nigeria devalued the official exchange rate in early July to 381 naira per US$1 from 360. --Herald--